HEADWORD: Marver
<hw>Mar"ver</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Prob. corrupt. fr.
OE. or F. <ets>marbre</ets> marble.]</ety> <fld>(Glass Marking)</fld>
<def>A stone, or cast-iron plate, or former, on which hot glass is
rolled to give it shape.</def>⟦br⟧
